        <properties>
          <explanationtextashtml>False</explanationtextashtml>
          <fieldcaption>{$digitalmarketing.emails.edit.subject$}</fieldcaption>
          <fielddescriptionashtml>False</fielddescriptionashtml>
          <includeincontentgeneration>True</includeincontentgeneration>
        </properties>
        <settings>
          <controlname>Kentico.Administration.TextInput</controlname>
        </settings>
        <validationrulesdata>
          <ValidationRuleConfiguration>
            <ValidationRuleIdentifier>Kentico.Administration.RequiredValue</ValidationRuleIdentifier>
            <RuleValues />
          </ValidationRuleConfiguration>
        </validationrulesdata>
        <additionalactionsdata>
          <AdditionalActionConfiguration>
            <AdditionalActionIdentifier>Kentico.Administration.AiraTextGeneration</AdditionalActionIdentifier>
            <AdditionalActionValues>
              <FieldDescription>
<![CDATA[
Email subject line.

Length: Mobile shows 33–50 chars, desktop up to 70. Avg is 6 words, but 2–4 word subject lines outperform — shorter = more attention-grabbing.
Front-load: Put the value/hook first — truncation cuts from the right.
Complement preview text: Subject = hook/title, preview = extension. Never repeat each other.
Personalization: First name alone doesn't move the needle much — deeper segmentation + behavioral relevance drives real lift.
Action-oriented language: Lead with a strong verb. "Start learning Python today" vastly outperforms "Python course information." 
Urgency/scarcity: Must be authentic and specific — vague "ends soon" doesn't work; concrete deadlines do. False urgency destroys trust.
Curiosity/questions: Prompts recipients to think and opens with the expectation of an answer — but the email must deliver on the premise or you erode trust.
Spam triggers to avoid: Multiple exclamation points, excessive emojis, ALL CAPS — max 1 emoji, and it should supplement words, not replace them.
]]>
              </FieldDescription>
            </AdditionalActionValues>
          </AdditionalActionConfiguration>
        </additionalactionsdata>
      </field>
      <field allowempty="true" column="EmailPreviewText" columnprecision="0" columntype="longtext" enabled="true" guid="6188e091-d4ce-4d3a-b824-b93bbb68f0c0" visible="true">
        <properties>
          <explanationtextashtml>False</explanationtextashtml>
          <fieldcaption>{$digitalmarketing.emails.edit.previewtext$}</fieldcaption>
          <fielddescription>
            <![CDATA[{$digitalmarketing.emails.edit.previewtext.tooltip$}]]>
          </fielddescription>
          <fielddescriptionashtml>False</fielddescriptionashtml>
          <includeincontentgeneration>True</includeincontentgeneration>
        </properties>
        <settings>
          <controlname>Kentico.Administration.TextArea</controlname>
        </settings>
        <additionalactionsdata>
          <AdditionalActionConfiguration>
            <AdditionalActionIdentifier>Kentico.Administration.AiraTextGeneration</AdditionalActionIdentifier>
            <AdditionalActionValues>
              <FieldDescription>
<![CDATA[
Email preview text.

Length: 40–90 chars. Mobile truncates early, so front-load the most useful context.
Complement, don't repeat: Subject line + preview text should work together. If the subject is the hook, the preview should add context about the issue's highlights.
Focus on value: Signal what readers will get from this newsletter issue, such as featured articles, useful links, or community discussions.
]]>
              </FieldDescription>
            </AdditionalActionValues>
          </AdditionalActionConfiguration>
        </additionalactionsdata>
      </field>
